    {'text': 'shows that the speed of the object is decreasing with time. The speed after 5s is -1 -1 4 ms and it becomes 2 ms after 10 s. as acceleration = slope of CD Speed-time graph in figure 2.24 gives negative \uf02d2 slope. Thus, the object has deceleration of 0.4 ms . DISTANCE TRAVELLED BY A MOVING OBJECT The area under a speed-time graph represents the distance travelled by the object. If the motion is uniform then the area can be calculated using appropriate formula for geometrical shapes represented by the graph. EXAMPLE 2.9 A car moves in a straight', 'page': 43},
