    {'text': 'Unit 7: Properties of Matter Physics 166 (iii) A gold bar of mass 0.2 kg. The density of gold is \uf02d3 \uf02d5 3 19300 kgm . (1.04x10 m ) -3 7.4 The density of air is 1.3 kgm . Find the mass of air in a room measuring 8m x 5m x 4m. (208 kg) 7.5 A student presses her palm by her thumb with a force of 75 N. How much would be the pressure under her thumb having contact 2 area 1.5 cm ? 5 \uf02d2 (5x10 Nm ) 7.6 The head of a pin is a square', 'page': 166},
    {'text': 'of side 10 mm. Find the pressure on it due to a force of 20 N. 5 \uf02d2 (2x10 Nm ) 7.7 A uniform rectangular block of wood 20 cm x 7.5 cm x 7.5 cm and of mass 1000g stands on a horizontal surface with its longest edge vertical. Find (i) the pressure exerted by the block on the surface (ii) density of the wood. \uf02d2 \uf02d3 (1778 Nm , 889 kgm ) 7.8 A cube of glass of 5 cm side and mass 306 g, has a cavity inside it. If the density of glass is \uf02d3 2.55', 'page': 166},
